item.title: Wisdom teeth
item.dc:creator: @Frell Frell
item.description:
@Frell wrote:

told me I needed mine out because they were tilted and I had no room. The surgeon told me within 2 seconds of looking in my mouth so I was skeptical. Said I should just get all 4 out.

Then saw they wanted $3k and knew why he didn’t give a fuk

6 months later a different dentist just said if they bother me I might need only the bottom two out

Left them in and my right bottom one came in straight (can feel entire surface with my tongue), left still on the way. I take care of them though, first place I brush every time and do it really thoroughly. I also use two sips of mouthwash for each one

item.title: Wisdom teeth
item.dc:creator: @stCky stCky
item.description:
@stCky wrote:

[quote=“Vain_, post:8, topic:550828”]cant remember what drugs i was prescribed but all four of my wisdon teeth grew in sideways and compacted inside my jawbone so i actually had part of my jaw cut/drilled out to get the teeth removed.

all i remember is getting the shot in my mouth and i instantly passed out. the pain wasnt too bad tbh with the drugs. it was just really sore and i couldnt eat anything without throwing up. everyone said to eat soup or crackers or ice-cream or jello. but i could barely drink water without it touching my where they cut me open and id instantly throw up :([/quote]

This is my biggest problem, eating and getting to sleep.

It turns out only one of my wisdom teeth is causing a problem, where it’s only 90% come through and the gum around it gets food stuck which goes rotten causing an infection. Infection == swelling == pressure on all my teeth.

I could get it removed, but am waiting to see if it’s going to keep causing issues.

Fuck, trying to eat is such a pain.

item.title: Wisdom teeth
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

Bowser jr:

Do you get any special drugs? I just took normal painkillers for the pain.

I was on Oxycodone or Hydrocodone for around 5 days, not sure which.

Many surgeons will also have you take some form of a benzodiazepine or benzo for short (I believe I was given Ativan) prior to surgery to help relax you. Benzo’s are used to treat anxiety so they relax you (usually). Unfortunately for me I’m taking max dosage of a benzo on a daily basis so the smaller pre-surgery benzo didn’t do anything to me.

In my case I was injected with three substances. I shut my eyes for a few seconds and then I woke up after the surgery. Whatever they use it packs one hell of a punch.
